tldr: The user requested a comprehensive aesthetic review and improvement for
  their sleep questionnaire app. I implemented a new sleep-themed design,
  ensuring consistent styling across all components and sections, and also fixed
  a console error related to null input values.
overview: "The user wanted to elevate the visual appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which initially had a generic and template-driven look. I
  began by analyzing the existing design, identifying areas for improvement in
  color, typography, layout, and form elements. The approach involved a
  multi-step implementation: first, establishing a new sleep-themed color
  palette and updating core UI components and the main form layout. This
  included adding subtle background effects, redesigning the progress indicator,
  and enhancing interactive form fields. During the process, a console error
  regarding  input values was identified and fixed by modifying the
   component to safely handle such values. Subsequently, I ensured design
  consistency by applying the new styling to all questionnaire sections,
  replacing old gray boxes with refined, themed card-style groupings. The final
  phase involved further polishing by introducing themed alert classes and
  increasing the opacity of section borders, resulting in a cohesive,
  professional, and calming user interface."
